I&rsquo;m currently in the process of moving the Alamo Coders website to DotNetNuke and I&rsquo;m being introduced to the details of DNN.
By default, the RSS Module isn&rsquo;t HTML friendly. However, by adding the following to an xsl tag:
value-of disable-output-escaping=&ldquo;yes&rdquo;
Example: Before: &lt;xsl:value-of select=&ldquo;description&rdquo;/&gt; After: &lt;xsl:value-of disable-output-escaping=&ldquo;yes&rdquo; select=&ldquo;description&rdquo;/&gt;
This allows for HTML encoding in your RSS feed.
