After reading a post by Scott Guthrie on the new C# Orcas language features I decided to download Orcas and try them out. (excited)
The new features I practiced with and love are:
Object initializers Example: Prior to Orcas: Person person = new Person(); person.FirstName = &ldquo;Scott&rdquo;; person.LastName = &ldquo;Guthrie&rdquo;; person.Age = 32;
Orcas:
Person person = new Person { FirstName=&ldquo;Scott&rdquo;, LastName=&ldquo;Guthrie&rdquo;, Age=32 };
I personally like this because I like to have a constructor initializer for all my objects.
